{"еұҘдҝ®жңҹ": "жҳҘеӯҰжңҹ", "дё»гҒӘж•ҷжҺҲиЁҖиӘһ": "иӢұиӘһ", "жҺҲжҘӯзӣ®зҡ„": "1. To develop studentsвҖҷ English proficiency through the study of academic topics in the field of sociology.2. To build studentsвҖҷ confidence in using English as a communicative tool.3. To help students improve their listening and note-taking skills through extensive lecture-listening activities.&nbsp;4. To introduce students to significant vocabulary words relevant to a wide range of academic topics.&nbsp;5. To prepare students to actively take part in discussions, teaching them the fundamental skills for agreeing and disagreeing with othersвҖҷ opinions.", "еҲ°йҒ”зӣ®жЁҷ": "1. Students will develop their academic skills.&nbsp;2. Students will become more confident and effective communicators.3. Students will strengthen their listening comprehension, note-taking and discussion skills.4. Students will acquire new vocabulary that will enhance their academic achievement.", "зү№иЁҳдәӢй …": "", "й–ўйҖЈз§‘зӣ®": "English Communication C 43", "жҺҲжҘӯгҒ®жҰӮиҰҒгғ»иғҢжҷҜ": "", "жҺҲжҘӯж–№жі•": "1. This course will be conducted in English only and English will be the means of communication between the students and the instructor.&nbsp;&nbsp;(Students will also be expected to communicate with one another in English.)2. Students are encouraged to actively participate in class discussions, both independently and collaboratively, in order to enhance their competence and confidence in English and also to create a better learning environment for all.&nbsp;", "гғҲгғ”гғғгӮҜ": {"з¬¬1еӣһ": ["<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin:0mm;font-size:medium;font-family:Cambria,serif;\"><span пҪҚпҪ“=\"пҪҚпҪ“\" жҳҺжңқ\";\"=\"жҳҺжңқ';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">гҖҗ</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">Startup Week</span><span пҪҚпҪ“=\"пҪҚпҪ“\" жҳҺжңқ\";\"=\"жҳҺжңқ';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">гҖ‘гғӘгғіг