e=\"margin:0mm;font-size:medium;font-family:Cambria,serif;\"><span пҪҚпҪ“=\"пҪҚпҪ“\" жҳҺжңқ\";\"=\"жҳҺжңқ';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">гҖҗ</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">Flex Hours</span><span пҪҚпҪ“=\"пҪҚпҪ“\" жҳҺжңқ\";\"=\"жҳҺжңқ';'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">гҖ‘</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin:0mm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif;font-size:11pt;\">Online class</span><span пҪҚпҪ“=\"пҪҚпҪ“\" жҳҺжңқ\";\"=\"жҳҺжңқ';'\" style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif;font-size:11pt;\">пјҲ</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif;font-size:11pt;\">On-demand format</span><span пҪҚпҪ“=\"пҪҚпҪ“\" жҳҺжңқ\";\"=\"жҳҺжңқ';'\" style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif;font-size:11pt;\">пјүпјҸ</span><span style=\"font-family:Cambria, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.6667px;\">гҖҠ20 minutesгҖӢ</span></span></p><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">Course Review &amp; Reflection</span>", ""], "жҺҲжҘӯеӨ–еӯҰзҝ’2": "<span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">One to two hours of homework can be expected each week. Students will be asked to watch course materials online, mostly lecture videos, throughout the semester. гҖҖгҖҖ</span>"}, "и©•дҫЎ": {"ж•ҷз§‘жӣё/Required texts0": ["Contemporary Topics Introductory&nbsp;(Supplementary materials will be provided by the instructor whenever needed.)Students are encouraged to bring a dictionary to class."], "ж•ҷз§‘жӣё/Required texts1": ["Jeanette Clement &amp; Cynthia Lennox", "Contemporary Topics Introductory (3rd Edition)", "Pearson Education, Inc.", "2009 е№ҙ", "9780132075176", ""], "еӯҰз”ҹгҒ«гӮҲгӮӢжҺҲжҘӯи©•дҫЎгҒ®ж–№жі•Course Evaluation by Students0": ["Students will independently evaluate the instructor and the course at the end of the semester."], "жҲҗзёҫи©•дҫЎGrading0": ["зЁ®еҲҘгҖҖTypeеӮҷиҖғгҖҖNote", "еүІеҗҲгҖҖPercentage", "и©•дҫЎеҹәжә–зӯүгҖҖGrading Criteria etc."], "жҲҗзёҫи©•дҫЎGrading1": ["гҒқгҒ®д»–пјҸOthers (99)", "100 %", "StudentsвҖҷ final grades will derive from a combination of assignments, activities, presentations, mini tests, etc."], "жҲҗзёҫи©•дҫЎGrading2": ["еӮҷиҖғгҖҖNote 1. Active participation is extremely important and counts as a significant part of studentsвҖҷ evaluation marks.&nbsp;&nbsp;2. Attendance is crucial to studentsвҖҷ success in this course. The instructor will carefully mark studentsвҖҷ attendance as&nbsp;present and on time, late,&nbsp;or&nbsp;absent.&nbsp;Specific rules regarding attendance are as follows:&nbsp;2a) Only students who are present at the time the class begins will receive full attendance marks.&nbsp;2b) Any student walking into the classroom after the class has begun will be marked late. The instructor will take this into account when giving students a participation grade.2c) Being 15 to 29 minutes late will equal half an absence (0.5).&nbsp;2d) Each time students are late 30 minutes or more, they will be marked&nbsp;absent.&nbsp;However, they are still encouraged to attend.&nbsp;&nbsp;2e) No more than three absences will be permitted in this course. Any student who is absent more than three times will automatically fail this course."], "еӮҷиҖғNote0": ["In principle, the use of smartphones, tablets, and other electronic devices in the classroom is forbidden. Students must store them in their bags throughout the entire duration of each class.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the case of a project in which internet connection is necessary, the instructor may instruct students to use their electronic devices, but unless such a situation is specifically and clearly suggested by the instructor, their use will be strictly prohibited."], "еӮҷиҖғNote1": ["2026е№ҙ04жңҲ26ж—Ҙ 10жҷӮ31еҲҶ01з§’"], "й …з•ӘNo.0": [], "й …з•ӘNo.1": ["2026е№ҙеәҰ", "жҳҘеӯҰжңҹпјҸSpring", "зҒ«жӣңпј“жҷӮйҷҗпјҸTuesday 3", "жҳҘеӯҰжңҹпјҸSpring", "пјҘпјҚпј“пјҗпј•"]}, "campas": 0, "name": "гҖҗ100гҖ‘English Communication пјЎгҖҖпј”пј“пјҸEnglish Communication A", "з®ЎзҗҶйғЁзҪІ": 2, "еҚҳдҪҚж•°": 1, "жӢ…еҪ“иҖ…": "жў…з”°гҖҖиӮҮпјҲUMEDA HAJIMEпјү ", "еұҘдҝ®еҹәжә–е№ҙеәҰ": "пј‘е№ҙ", "еұҘдҝ®зҷ»йҢІж–№жі•": "дәҲеӮҷзҷ»йҢІ", "з·ҠжҖҘжҺҲжҘӯеҪўж…Ӣ": 0, "й–Ӣи¬ӣжңҹ": 1, "жҷӮйҷҗ1": 9, "жҷӮйҷҗ1_term": 0, "и©•дҫЎ1": 6, "жҲҗзёҫи©•дҫЎеӮҷиҖғ": "еӮҷиҖғгҖҖNote\n1. Active participation is extremely important and counts as a significant part of studentsвҖҷ evaluation marks.  \n2. Attendance is crucial to studentsвҖҷ success in this course. The instructor will carefully mark studentsвҖҷ attendance as present and on time, late, or absent. Specific rules regarding attendance are as follows: \n2a) Only students who are present at the time the class begins will receive full attendance marks. \n2b) Any student walking into the classroom after the class has begun will be marked late. The instructor will take this into account when giving students a participation grade.\n2c) Being 15 to 29 minutes late will equal half an absence (0.5). \n2d) Each time students are late 30 minutes or more, they will be marked absent. However, they are still encouraged to attend.  \n2e) No more than three absences will be permitted in this course. Any student who is absent more than three times will automatically fail this course."}